 'Peep Show' writer reveals abandoned plans for a stage adaptation https://www.nme.com/news/tv/peep-show-writer-reveals-abandoned-plans-for-a-stage-adaptation-3502712?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=peep-show-writer-reveals-abandoned-plans-for-a-stage-adaptationChris Edwards Fri, 22 Sep 2023 14:46:25 +0000 NewsTV NewsChannel 4Peep Showhttps://www.nme.com/?p=3502712 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/Peep-Show-main.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="西洋镜" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/Peep-Show-main.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/Peep-Show-main-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/Peep-Show-main-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/Peep-Show-main-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/Peep-Show-main-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/Peep-Show-main-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> &quot;We just couldn&#39;t get our heads around how it would be &#39;Peep Show&#39; on stage&quot;</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/tv/peep-show-writer-reveals-abandoned-plans-for-a-stage-adaptation-3502712">&#39;Peep Show&#39; writer reveals abandoned plans for a stage adaptation</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/Peep-Show-main.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="西洋镜" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/Peep-Show-main.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/Peep-Show-main-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/Peep-Show-main-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/Peep-Show-main-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/Peep-Show-main-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/Peep-Show-main-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/series/peep-show"><em>Peep Show</em></a> co-writer Sam Bain has revealed that they received offers to turn the hit <a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/channel-4">Channel 4</a> sitcom into a play.</p><ul class="post-content-read-more"><li> <strong>READ MORE: <a href="https://www.nme.com/blogs/tv-blogs/best-peep-show-moments-mitchell-webb-2141159">Mitchell &amp; Webb&#39;s favourite <em>Peep Show</em> moments</a></strong></li></ul><p> Speaking exclusively to <a href="https://www.nme.com/features/tv-interviews/peep-show-interview-david-mitchell-robert-webb-3501235"><em>NME</em></a> , Bain said that he and fellow co-writer Jesse Armstrong ( <a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/succession"><em>Succession</em></a> ) had to reject the proposal because they couldn&#39;t figure out how to make the show work on stage.</p><p> Now celebrating its 20th anniversary, <em>Peep Show</em> documented the increasingly tragic lives of bank manager Mark Corrigan (played by David Mitchell) and his layabout flatmate/ occasional musician Jeremy Usborne (played by Robert Webb).</p><p> The iconic comedy was shot through a POV perspective with the actors performing to camera, while the characters&#39; internal thoughts were added as narration. This format proved to be revolutionary, but it was one Bain and Armstrong knew they wouldn&#39;t be able to replicate on stage.</p><p> “There was an offer to do a live <em>Peep Show</em> , a stage show, after the last series, which we did carefully consider because it was coming from some proper people,” said Bain. “But we just, we just couldn&#39;t get our heads around how it would be <em>Peep Show</em> on stage. And I think with that sort of thing, we&#39;d want to be careful.”</p><p> Referring to the POV camera angle used in the show, he added: “You sort of can&#39;t [make that work on stage] and then it becomes something very different, and then it&#39;s like, &#39;What are we doing?&#39; But yeah, that was our thought process at the time, I think.” </p><figure id="attachment_2855889" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-2855889" style="width: 956px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-2855889" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/2015PeepShow_2015_090915.jpg" alt="西洋镜" width="956" height="634" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/2015PeepShow_2015_090915.jpg 956w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/2015PeepShow_2015_090915-400x265.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/2015PeepShow_2015_090915-800x531.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/2015PeepShow_2015_090915-696x462.jpg 696w" sizes="(max-width: 956px) 100vw, 956px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-2855889" class="wp-caption-text"> &#39;Peep Show&#39; first aired in 2003. Credit: Channel 4</figcaption></figure><p> Elsewhere, in a piece reflecting on the show&#39;s legacy with <em><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/sep/18/the-scripts-were-the-funniest-things-id-ever-read-the-stars-of-peep-show-look-back-20-years-later" target="_blank" rel="noopener">The Guardian</a></em> , script editor Iain Morris explained how <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/tv/ricky-gervais-saved-peep-show-from-being-cancelled-3500538">Ricky Gervais helped save the series from being cancelled</a> in its infancy.</p><p> “[Channel 4] hated it because it wasn&#39;t rating and they didn&#39;t really understand it,” Morris explained. “I spent a lot of time defending it, probably to the detriment of my career.”</p><p> Gervais, however, was one of the show&#39;s big early supporters, and helped the network decide to keep it on air.</p><p> “He kept talking about it. Because <a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/the-office"><em>The Office</em></a> was so huge, his love for <em>Peep Show</em> effectively got it recommissioned.”</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/tv/peep-show-writer-reveals-abandoned-plans-for-a-stage-adaptation-3502712">&#39;Peep Show&#39; writer reveals abandoned plans for a stage adaptation</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
